<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Silverblade-T-E</div><div class="date">November 19th, 2011, 04:49 AM</div></div><div class="posttext">1) Brillaint fix for the map!<br />
this removes clouds and blur, lets you rotate map (right mouse button) even to go up and see sky above! ;)<br />
<br />
add this to end of your skyrim.ini file (in my documents/games/skyrim, usually and of course BACK UP YOUR ORIGINL INI FILE!)<br />
<br />
<br />
[MapMenu]<br />
sMapCloudNIF=0<br />
fMapWorldMaxHeight=150000.0000<br />
fMapWorldMinHeight=8000.0000<br />
bWorldMapNoSkyDepthBlur=1<br />
fWorldMapDepthBlurScale=0<br />
fMapWorldZoomSpeed=0.3700<br />
fMapWorldMaxPitch=400.0000<br />
fMapWorldYawRange=400.0000<br />
<br />
<br />
2) Turn off ALL antialiasing maybe turn of anisotropic filtering too<br />
go to ADVANCED tab, turn on FXAA<br />
should massively improve performance, lets me run Ultra on 240GT card, heeh<br />
<br />
3) to improve game perdormance on PC with 64 bit/lots of RAM<br />
<br />
<br />
Open skyrim.ini, and check for [Papyrus] section. If it's not present, just create one at the end of the file. <br />
Add iMinMemoryPageSize=100000 and iMaxMemoryPageSize=5000000 <br />
Add iMaxAllocatedMemoryBytes=1800000000 <br />
WARNING! Do not increase iMaxAllocatedMemoryBytes value, because memory fragmentation may cause the game to crash or freeze. <br />
<br />
<br />
4) Post Process injector<br />
when FXAA is turned on, this mod lets gorgeous effects be added, sharpen, saturate, desaturate etc<br />
I love ++ saturation in my art work<br />
alas, screenshots from inside game cannot show this effect due to way it's done (not even Steam's F12 key), only external capture program can show it so you'd need ot use FRAPS, PaintShopPro etc to get gorgeous screengrabs :(<br />
<br />
http://skyrimnexus.com/downloads/file.php?id=131<br />
<br />
this image (if link works) shows heavy saturation on<br />
<br />
http://skyrimnexus.com/downloads/images/131-1-1321216439.png<br />
<br />
5) add rock/tree self shadowing<br />
edit SkyrimPrefs.ini<br />
(note, PREFS, and again back up first!) <br />
<br />
<br />
Change bDrawLandShadows=0 to bDrawLandShadows=1 <br />
Change bTreesReceiveShadows=0 to bTreesReceiveShadows=1<br />
<br />
:)<br />
<br />
(new thread for clarity)</div></div><hr />


