<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Ackar</div><div class="date">November 30th, 2011, 06:28 AM</div></div><div class="posttext">Skyrim Character Manager (http://www.skyrimnexus.com/downloads/file.php?id=2119)<br />
<br />
<br />
How it Works:<br />
It stores your character info in separate folders under the &quot;My Games\Skyrim&quot; folder in your &quot;My Documents&quot; folder. This allows you to switch easily between characters.<br />
<br />
Pre-installation:<br />
If you already have multiple characters in the &quot;Saves&quot; folder, then you will have to manually sort the save files into distinct folders before you run it. <br />
<br />
If you have to seperate your characters like this then make sure the last save is not an auto or quicksave just to be sure. I'd also recommend making a backup first.<br />
<br />
This task shouldn't be too difficult because the saves generally have the name of each character (except autosave and quick save).<br />
<br />
Once this is done, name the folders according to your character, but leave at least one character folder named &quot;Saves&quot;, this will be needed when the program first runs.</div></div><hr />


