<br />
Not at all.  Imagine if your monitor was just a frame.  If you held the frame really close to your face, you would be able to see a huge angle to either side.  If you held the screen back a few feet, the angle you could see would be much smaller.  That is what causes problems with the FOV: When you're drastically outside of the distance your brain expects for the angle, it can cause headaches, or nausea.</div></div><hr />


